<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Twitter | Ramon Gomes da Silva</title><link>https://ramongss.github.io/tag/twitter/</link><atom:link href="https://ramongss.github.io/tag/twitter/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><description>Twitter</description><generator>Wowchemy (https://wowchemy.com)</generator><language>en-us</language><copyright>Â© 2023 Ramon G. da Silva</copyright><lastBuildDate>Fri, 29 Oct 2021 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><image><url>https://ramongss.github.io/media/icon_hu04e5c2b3c4d5324d70c5660218839495_17254_512x512_fill_lanczos_center_3.png</url><title>Twitter</title><link>https://ramongss.github.io/tag/twitter/</link></image><item><title>covibrasilbot</title><link>https://ramongss.github.io/project/covidbrasilbot/</link><pubDate>Fri, 29 Oct 2021 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://ramongss.github.io/project/covidbrasilbot/</guid><description>&lt;p>The Twitter bot &lt;a href="https://www.twitter.com/covidbrasilbot" target="_blank" rel="noopener">@covidbrasilbot&lt;/a> posts daily reports about the number of confirmed cases and deaths caused by COVID-19 in Brazil using &lt;a href="https://docs.ropensci.org/rtweet/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">{rtweet}&lt;/a> and &lt;a href="https://docs.github.com/en/actions" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub Actions&lt;/a>.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>In the &lt;a href="https://github.com/ramongss/covidbrasilbot/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Github Repo&lt;/a> contains a &lt;a href="https://github.com/features/actions" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub Action&lt;/a> that runs on schedule (every day at 00:30 UTC). It executes the R code that retrieves the COVID-19 data from &lt;a href="https://twitter.com/brasil_io" target="_blank" rel="noopener">@brasil_io&lt;/a>, summarizes the information, generates the graphs with the confirmed cases and deaths info, and creates a &amp;ldquo;micro-report&amp;rdquo; to be posted. The report and the graphs are posted to &lt;a href="https://www.twitter.com/covidbrasilbot" target="_blank" rel="noopener">@covidbrasilbot&lt;/a> on Twitter using &lt;a href="https://docs.ropensci.org/rtweet/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">{rtweet}&lt;/a> package.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>The &lt;a href="https://www.twitter.com/covidbrasilbot" target="_blank" rel="noopener">@covidbrasilbot&lt;/a> was inspired by my other &lt;a href="https://ramongss.github.io/project/covid19-autoreport/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">COVID-19 AutoReport Project&lt;/a> and the &lt;a href="https://twitter.com/londonmapbot" target="_blank" rel="noopener">@londonmapbot&lt;/a> created by &lt;a href="https://twitter.com/mattdray" target="_blank" rel="noopener">@mattdray&lt;/a>.&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>